               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Hidāyat al-iksīr by ʿAbd al-Hādī ibn ʿAbd al-Ḥafīẓ</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85003265 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007100968 "
                     n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_872-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Compendious treatise on the knowledge of the ancients, covering alchemy
                           and elixirs, as well as early Arabic eulogies, by <persName
                              key="person_f8046" role="aut">ʿAbd al-Hādī ibn ʿAbd
                              al-Ḥafīẓ</persName> of <placeName>Muṣṭafá'ābād</placeName> (present
                           Rāmpūr, UP), in the sarkār of Sihrind (Sirhind), who wrote the work in
                           1178/1764-5 to inform his contemporaries. </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. </p>
                        <p>Heavily annotated in parts. </p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8046">ʿAbd al-Hādī ibn ʿAbd
                           al-Ḥafīẓ</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f8046">عبد الهادى ابن عبد
                           الحفيظ</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23203">Hidāyat al-iksīr</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23203">هداية الاكسير</title>
                  </msItem>
